        "goseg/protocol/contracts/protocolfamily/specs.go",
        "goseg/uploadsvc/contractspec/specs.go",
        "goseg/protocol/contracts/family_specs_test.go",
        "goseg/uploadsvc/contractspec/contractspec_test.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`ProtocolActionContractRoot` is defined in both protocolfamily and uploadsvc contractspec packages.",
        "Both packages construct contract IDs by string concatenation with local constants, creating parallel sources of truth for naming and ID shape.",
        "Alignment is validated after the fact by integration-style tests rather than by shared type/constructor ownership."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Extract contract identity primitives (root, namespace/action keys, ID constructor/validator) into a single shared contracts boundary package and make feature packages supply only domain-specific entries. Keep one canonical constructor for action contract IDs and reuse it from both protocol and uploadsvc specs.",
      "confidence": "high",
      "impact_scope": "subsystem",
      "fix_scope": "architectural_change",
      "root_cause_cluster": "fragmented_contract_model"
    },
    {
      "dimension": "cross_module_architecture",
      "identifier": "parallel_spec_models_without_common_contract_schema",
      "summary": "Multiple near-identical spec structs across modules indicate a missing shared contract schema boundary.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/protocol/contracts/protocolfamily/specs.go",
        "goseg/uploadsvc/contractspec/specs.go",
        "goseg/protocol/contracts/startramfamily/specs.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`ActionSpec`, `UploadActionSpec`, and `ContractSpec` all encode overlapping metadata (`ID/ContractID`, name, description, owner) with inconsistent field shape.",
        "The schema divergence forces mapping/validation glue in tests and contract assembly paths, rather than direct reuse of one cross-module model.",
        "This pattern increases coupling via coordination overhead whenever metadata requirements change (e.g., governance fields, message fields)."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Define a single canonical spec DTO in `protocol/contracts` (with optional typed extensions where needed) and have family-specific packages return that shared shape. Add package-level constructors/adapters so cross-module wiring composes one model instead of parallel structs.",
      "confidence": "medium",
      "impact_scope": "subsystem",
      "fix_scope": "multi_file_refactor",
      "root_cause_cluster": "fragmented_contract_model"
    }
  ],
  "retrospective": {
    "root_causes": [
      "Contract boundary ownership is distributed across feature packages instead of centralized in one architectural contract module.",
      "Schema duplication has been tolerated and backstopped by tests, masking architectural drift until validation time."
    ],
    "likely_symptoms": [
      "duplicated_contract_identity_boundary",
      "parallel_spec_models_without_common_contract_schema"
